'''Orbicules''' (syn. [[Ubisch]] bodies, con-peito grains) are small acellular structures of [[sporopollenin]] (known size range from < 1&nbsp;µm to 15&nbsp;µm, but usually sub-micrometre) that might occur on the inner tangential and radial walls of [[Tapetum (botany)|tapetal cells]]. Their function is unclear at this moment. Current consensus is that they are just a by-product of pollen wall sporopollenin synthesis.
